From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dimitris Panokostas <midwan@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Jun 2026 20:10:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] uae: implement and export ppc_cpu_flush_jit (vcpu safe-point)

AmigaOS 3.x / WarpOS patches PPC code+page tables directly in shared RAM,
bypassing QEMU's PPC softmmu, so the PPC runs stale TBs/translations and the
m68k<->PPC handshake deadlocks (BlitterStudio/amiberry#2114). The old qemu-uae
plugin exported ppc_cpu_flush_jit; the QEMU 11 port dropped it. Reinstate +
export it. In QEMU 11 a synchronous flush is only legal on the vcpu in serial
context, so ppc_cpu_flush_jit() (called by UAE from the m68k thread at an
m68k->PPC handoff) only sets the global uae_flush_requested flag; the PPC vcpu
consumes it synchronously at a cpu_exec() safe point (see the cpu-exec patch).
---
 uae/qemu-uae-cpu.c        | 13 +++++++++++++
 uae/qemu-uae-ld64.symbols |  1 +
 uae/qemu-uae.symbols      |  1 +
 3 files changed, 15 insertions(+)

--- a/uae/qemu-uae-cpu.c
+++ b/uae/qemu-uae-cpu.c
@@ -343,6 +343,17 @@
     return result;
 }
 
+/*
+ * Set by UAE (from the m68k thread, via ppc_cpu_flush_jit) when the m68k has
+ * patched PPC code or page tables directly in shared RAM (#2114). It is consumed
+ * by the PPC vcpu thread at a cpu_exec() safe point (accel/tcg/cpu-exec.c), the
+ * only place a flush can run SYNCHRONOUSLY in QEMU 11: a flush from the m68k
+ * thread either asserts (not a vcpu in serial context) or, done async, lands too
+ * late and the WarpOS handshake has already desynced. Global so cpu-exec.c can
+ * read it.
+ */
+int uae_flush_requested;
+
 void PPCAPI ppc_cpu_run_continuous(void)
 {
     uae_log("QEMU: Running main loop\n");
@@ -388,6 +399,11 @@
     }
 }
 
+void PPCAPI ppc_cpu_flush_jit(void)
+{
+    qatomic_set(&uae_flush_requested, 1);
+}
+
 static void qemu_uae_log_cpu_state(void)
 {
     int flags = 0;
--- a/uae/qemu-uae.symbols
+++ b/uae/qemu-uae.symbols
@@ -1,5 +1,6 @@
 {
   global:
+    ppc_cpu_flush_jit;
     ppc_cpu_init;
     ppc_cpu_map_memory;
     ppc_cpu_reset;
--- a/uae/qemu-uae-ld64.symbols
+++ b/uae/qemu-uae-ld64.symbols
@@ -1,3 +1,4 @@
+_ppc_cpu_flush_jit
 _ppc_cpu_init
 _ppc_cpu_map_memory
 _ppc_cpu_reset
